    <chapter xml:id="functions-of-multiple-variables">
      <title>Functions of Multiple Variables Introduction</title>
        <introduction>
         <p>In this unit we will be learning about functions of multiple variables. 
            This includes functions of two or three variables, as well as vector-valued 
            functions. In this module we will be learning the basic tools for working 
            with these functions, including how to visualize them, how to perform basic 
            operations, and how to apply these concepts to solve problems.</p>
            <p>There are five learning outcomes for this unit:
            <ul>
                <li><p>FUN-1 Vector Applications</p></li>
                <li><p>FUN-2 Equations of Lines and Planes</p></li>
                <li><p>FUN-3 Surfaces in Space</p></li>
                <li><p>FUN-4 Vector Functions</p></li>
                <li><p>FUN-5 Functions of Several Variables</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        </introduction>
        <xi:include href="./fun-outcomes/fun1-materials.ptx" />
        <xi:include href="./fun-outcomes/fun2-materials.ptx" />
        <!-- etc. -->
    </chapter>

    <chapter xml:id="differential-calculus">
      <title>Differential Calculus</title>

      <introduction>
        <p>
         There are six learning outcomes for this unit:
         <ul>
          <li><p>DC-1 Partial Derivatives</p></li>
          <li><p>DC-2 Tangent Lines and Linear Approximations</p></li>
          <li><p>DC-3 The Chain Rule</p></li>
          <li><p>DC-4 Directional Derivatives</p></li>
          <li><p>DC-5 Maximum and Minimum Values</p></li>
          <li><p>DC-6 Lagrange Multipliers</p></li> 
         </ul>
        </p>
      </introduction>
        <xi:include href="./notes/week02.ptx"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </chapter>

    <chapter xml:id="integral-calculus">
      <title>Integral Calculus</title>

      <introduction>
        <p>
         There are five learning outcomes for this unit:
         <ul>
          <li><p>IC-1 Double Integrals</p></li>
          <li><p>IC-2 Double Integrals in Polar Coordinates</p></li>
          <li><p>IC-3 Triple Integrals</p></li>
          <li><p>IC-4 Integrals for Mass and Center of Mass</p></li>
          <li><p>IC-5 Change of Variables</p></li> 
         </ul>
        </p>
      </introduction>
        <xi:include href="./homework/homework-01.ptx"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </chapter>
    
    <chapter xml:id="applications-of-multivariable-calculus">
      <title>Applications of Multivariable Calculus</title>

      <introduction>
        <p>
         There are six learning outcomes for this unit:
         <ul>
          <li><p>APP-1 Line Integrals</p></li>
          <li><p>APP-2 Vector Fields</p></li>
          <li><p>APP-3 Green's Theorem</p></li>
          <li><p>APP-4 Surface Integrals</p></li>
          <li><p>APP-5 Stokes' Theorem</p></li>
          <li><p>APP-6 Divergence Theorem</p></li> 
         </ul>
        </p>
      </introduction>
        <xi:include href="./homework/homework-template.ptx"/>
